RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $20,000 In Their Last Three Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VOODOO MISTRESS broke on top to set a pressured pace around the first turn, went to a clear lead to late stretch, dug in and held off the late closers and prevailed. LILY'S CREED tracked the leaders down the backstretch, saved ground around the final turn then angled out in upper stretch to gain late on the winner and proved second best. JU JU VIP was allowed to settle around the first turn then made a middle move on the backstretch and made a rail bid around the final turn for a late run at the top two but was too late. CAJUN TRINITY pressed the pace around the first turn then chased the winner home. SHE'S MY LOUIE V. was forwardly place around the first turn while racing three wide and tired. LYRICAL MUSIC was five wide into the first turn then raced near the back and was never a threat. PREACH IT GIRL went six wide into the first turn and raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Lily's Creed
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, saved ground, angled out, late gain

ENTRY.NAME: Ju Ju Vip
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, middle move, rail bid, late run, too late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOHNNY JUDE pressed the pace from the two path then engaged the leader at the three sixteenths pole, dueled down the stretch and prevailed. SHANKINSTINE went the the front to set the pace, was challenged at the eighth pole, dueled down the stretch and gave way grudgingly. ANGOLA VACATION was off the pace around the first turn but failed to menace. KAT'S SOLDIER was unhurried around the first turn moved up four wide at the three eighths pole but was not a threat. RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 99. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 37000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MAY 25, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE AT A MILE OR OVER SINCE JULY 25 OR CLAIMING PRICE $32,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 25 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since November 25 Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Claiming Races For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEXICAN WONDER BOY went to the lead to set all the pace, was challenged from outside rival at the five sixteenths, dueled around the final turn and in the stretch drive, drifted out and bumped PIPES AND DRUMS in late stretch but kept on and just lasted, took a bad step after the wire and was vanned off. PIPES AND DRUMS was allowed to settle around the first turn in the middle of the pack then moved up three wide on the backstretch, engaged the leader at the five sixteenths pole, battled around the turn and down the stretch, was bumped by MEXICAN WONDER BOY and just missed. COSMIC TRAIN was unhurried down the backstretch then moved out to three wide at the quarter pole but was no match for the top two. JIMI'S A STAR saved ground throughout and passed tiring rival. MILITARY BEARING was placed off the pace around the first turn in the two path then moved between horses at the three eighths pole and retreated. TAPAGE was five wide into the first turn, was four wide into the backstretch while racing in the middle of the pack but gave way. INTIMIDATION was forwardly placed around the first turn from the three path and dropped back. JOCKEY OBJECTION, JOCKEY OF PIPES AND DRUMS CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF MEXICAN WONDER BOY FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN DEEP STRETCH, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

ENTRY.NAME: Mexican Wonder Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: led, stretch battle, drift, bump, just lasted, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Tapage
ENTRY.OWNER: Highfield Investment Group Inc and Appleyard Greg

ENTRY.NAME: Pipes and Drums
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, mid pack, 3wbid, engaged5/16, bumped, missed
